<item>
            <title>[FLINK-6474] Potential loss of precision in 32 bit integer multiplication</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-6474</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In TaskManagerServicesConfiguration#parseNetworkEnvironmentConfiguration&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (!hasNewNetworkBufConf(configuration)) {
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// map old config to &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; one:
&lt;/span&gt;      networkBufMin = networkBufMax = numNetworkBuffers * pageSize;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;networkBufMax is a long.&lt;br/&gt;
However the multiplication is done in 32 bit integer, leading to potential loss of precision.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
